BASIC SETUP:

Download source:
1.) $ svn co https://svn.research.cc.gatech.edu/kaos/khan/branches/media/
2.) cd into folder
3.) modify khan.cpp and khan.h for file location (khan_root)
4.) make/ make clean

SERVER SETUP:
1.) Start Redis Server
	- open terminal into /redis folder and go into /src folder
	- $ ./redis-server
	- open another terminal into /redis folder and go into /src folder
	- $ ./redis-cli
2.) Modify khan.cpp line 10 - to use redis

TESTING SETUP:
-- Mount Media Folder --
1.) Terminal operation
	$ mount /tmp/networkedFiles
1a.) mount as user to address some permission problems
1b.) go to /etc/fstab and add in the following (change ‘peter’ to appropriate user you want it to access/mount)

# 4shared.com webdav

https://webdav.4shared.com/ /tmp/networkedFiles davfs user,uid=peter,noauto,rw 0 0

2.) enter username and pass to access files


RUNNING:

-- Start up Redis Server --
1.) Start up server
	$ ./redis-server
1a.) (Optional) Open client to see what is contained in database
	$ ./redis-cli

-- Run Khan --
1.) make clean/make
2.) Set up folder
	$ mkdir /tmp/fuse
3.) Run khan
	$ ./khan /tmp/fuse
	$ ./khan /tmp/fuse -d (debug)
4.) for getting timings
    	$ mkdir stats (in /tmp/fuse)

-- While Running --
1.) Useful Redis Client Commands
    	$ redis … > keys *
        	Prints out a list of keys
    	$ redis … > get 12
        	Print out value for key 12
    	$ redis … > flushall
        	Clear out all keys in redis database
   
-- End/Clean up --

1.) when done:
    	$ umount /tmp/fuse/

-- Implemented Commands --
mkdir stats
mkdir refreshall
mkdir FOLDER.union.FOLDER
mkdir FOLDER.intersect.FOLDER
